{{Infobox artist | name = Dmitry Petrovich Buchkin | image = | imagesize = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = July 23, 1927 | birth_place = [[Leningrad]], [[USSR]] | death_date = | death_place = | field = [[Painting]] | citizenship = [[USSR]] | nationality = | training = [[Vera Mukhina Institute]] | movement = [[Realism (visual art)|Realism]] | works = | patrons = | awards = }}
'''Dmitry Petrovich Buchkin''' ({{lang-ru|Дмитрий Петрович Бучкин}}; July 23, 1927, [[Leningrad]], [[USSR]]) is a [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] [[Russians|Russian]] painter, a member of the [[Saint Petersburg Union of Artists]] (before 1992 — the Leningrad Union of Artists),<ref>''Справочник членов Ленинградской организации Союза художников РСФСР.'' Л., Художник РСФСР, 1987. C.20.</ref> who lives and works in [[Saint Petersburg]]. He is also regarded as one of the representatives of the [[Leningrad School of Painting|Leningrad school of painting]],<ref>''Sergei V. Ivanov. Unknown Socialist Realism. The Leningrad School.'' Saint Petersburg, NP-Print Edition, 2007. P.15, 389, 395, 397, 402, 405-407, 444.</ref> being best known for his genre and landscape paintings. In the 1960s and 1980s he repeatedly worked in the [[House of creativity «Staraya Ladoga»]], later he worked in his own cottage with his art studio in [[Staraya Ladoga]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://socrealizm.com.ua/gallery/artist/buchkin-dp-1927|title=Ленинградский художник Бучкин Дмитрий Петрович|last=|first=|date=|website=Socialist Realism. Kiev club of collectors.|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
