{{Infobox Artwork | image_file=corot.villedavray.750pix.jpg | title=Ville d’Avray | artist=Jean-Baptiste-Camille Corot | year=1865 | medium=oil on canvas | height_metric=65 | width_metric=49 | metric_unit=cm | imperial_unit=in | city=Washington D.C. | museum=[[National Gallery of Art]] }}
'''''Ville d’Avray''''' is an 1865 [[oil painting]] by [[France|French]] artist [[Jean-Baptiste-Camille Corot]]. It is currently on display at the [[National Gallery of Art]] in [[Washington D.C.]].
The painting is of the commune where Corot lived in [[Ville d'Avray]].
